## Package Managers

- JS dependencies: `npm` (`npm install`, `npm run dev`, `npm test`)
- Python dependencies: `uv` (`uv sync`, `uv add <pkg>`, `uv run <script>`)
- Never mix: do not use `pip` or `yarn`

## Backend Architecture

FastAPI + SQLite + Jinja2 (HTML shell only).

```
backend/
  main.py              FastAPI app — lifespan init_db, Jinja2 GET /, /static mount
  database.py          sqlite3 CRUD: init_db, get_all, create, update, delete
  models.py            Pydantic: TransactionIn, TransactionOut
  routers/
    transactions.py    /api/transactions — GET, POST, PUT/{id}, DELETE/{id}
  templates/
    index.html         Jinja2 shell — mounts React #root (production only)
```

API endpoints:
- `GET  /api/transactions[?type=&category=]` → `list[TransactionOut]`
- `POST /api/transactions` → `TransactionOut` (201)
- `PUT  /api/transactions/{id}` → `TransactionOut`
- `DELETE /api/transactions/{id}` → 204

`amount` is stored as `TEXT` in SQLite — do not cast to float in the DB layer.

Run dev stack: `uv run uvicorn backend.main:app --reload --port 8000` + `npm run dev` (Vite proxies `/api/*` to `:8000`).

## Component Architecture

`App.jsx` owns all shared state and handlers. Rendering is delegated to five components:

```
App
├── Summary               props: totalIncome, totalExpenses, balance
├── AddTransaction        props: categories, onSubmit(newTransaction)
│                         owns its own local form state; resets after submit
├── Transactions          props: transactions (pre-filtered), filterType, filterCategory,
│                                categories, onFilterTypeChange, onFilterCategoryChange,
│                                onUpdate(transaction), onDelete(id)
├── UpdateTransaction     props: transaction, categories, onConfirm(updatedTransaction), onCancel
│   └── ModalActions      props: visible, message, onConfirm, onCancel, children
│       └── .update-fields
│           ├── <input type="text">    description
│           ├── <input type="number">  amount
│           ├── <select>               type (income | expense)
│           └── <select>               category
└── ModalActions          props: visible, message, onConfirm, onCancel   ← Delete flow only
```

Component files live in `src/components/`. Do not add state to `Summary` or `Transactions` — they are stateless. `UpdateTransaction` owns its own form state and syncs from props via `useEffect`.

## State Ownership

**`App.jsx` (shared):** `transactions`, `filterType`, `filterCategory`, `pendingDeleteId`, `pendingUpdate`
- `transactions` is loaded from `GET /api/transactions` on mount via `useEffect([], getTransactions)`
- All CRUD handlers (`handleAdd`, `handleUpdateConfirm`, `handleDeleteConfirm`) are `async`; they call `src/api.js` then update local state optimistically
- `filterType` / `filterCategory` filtering is applied client-side before passing to `<Transactions>`

**`AddTransaction.jsx` (local form only):** `description`, `amount`, `type`, `category` — resets to defaults after submit

**`UpdateTransaction.jsx` (local form only):** `description`, `amount`, `type`, `category` — synced from `transaction` prop via `useEffect([transaction])`; validates non-empty description + numeric amount before calling `onConfirm(updatedTransaction)`

## Data Flow

```
React App.jsx
  → src/api.js (fetch wrappers)
    → GET/POST/PUT/DELETE /api/transactions
      → FastAPI routers/transactions.py
        → backend/database.py (sqlite3)
          → finance.db
```

`src/api.js` is the only file that references the `/api/transactions` URL. Do not inline `fetch` calls in components.

## Data Rules

- `amount` is stored as a **string** on every transaction object
- Always use `parseFloat(t.amount)` for arithmetic — never coerce with `+` or `Number()`
- `totalIncome`, `totalExpenses`, and `balance` are derived on every render in `App.jsx`; never store them in state

## Testing Rules

- Runner: Vitest 4 + jsdom; setup file `src/setupTests.js` imports `@testing-library/jest-dom` only — no localStorage mock
- API is mocked at the module level: `vi.mock('./api')` at the top of `App.test.jsx`
- `beforeEach` configures mocks and renders:
  ```js
  getTransactions.mockResolvedValue([...SEED_TRANSACTIONS])
  addTransaction.mockImplementation(t => Promise.resolve({ ...t, id: Date.now() }))
  updateTransaction.mockImplementation(t => Promise.resolve(t))
  deleteTransaction.mockResolvedValue(undefined)
  await act(async () => { render(<App />) })
  await waitFor(() => expect(getRowCount()).toBe(8))
  ```
- Async CRUD actions need `waitFor` on the expected DOM change — not just `await user.click`
- Always use `userEvent.setup()` — do not call `userEvent` methods directly (legacy API)
- Scope queries with `within(element)` to avoid cross-section matches
  - **Critical gotcha**: `screen.getByText('Income')` is ambiguous — matches the summary card `<h3>` AND `<option value="income">` elements. Always use `within(document.querySelector('.summary'))` first
- Seed data: 8 transactions; `[0]` = Salary (income, $5000), `[1]` = Rent (expense, $1200), `[2]` = Groceries (expense, $150)
  - Target `deleteButtons[1]` / `updateButtons[1]` for expense mutations; `updateButtons[2]` for Groceries (category tests)
- Inside the Update modal:
  - `getByPlaceholderText('Description')` → description text input
  - `getByRole('spinbutton')` → amount number input (unique; `type="number"`)
  - `getAllByRole('combobox')` → `[typeSelect, categorySelect]`

## Constraints

- No router, no React context, no external state library on the frontend
- No cloud/remote persistence — SQLite (`finance.db`) is local to the server process
- Do not inline `fetch` calls in React components — all API calls go through `src/api.js`
- Do not add ORM dependencies — use stdlib `sqlite3` directly in `backend/database.py`
